    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-07T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-07T14:00:00-05:00" n="119"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5197</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-07T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 8, 1.15 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6391. Your 4942, June 6, 6 p.m. <persName corresp="#p_NVA1"
                        >Northcliffe</persName> is sent on a purely commercial errand to supervise
                    the purchasing agents of the British Government in the United States. He has no
                    diplomatic errand or standing nor is he a “commissioner or commissioner general”
                    nor do his duties have any reference to what Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1"
                        >Balfour</persName> did.</p>
                <p>He knows the United States better than any Englishman except Bryce and he will
                    have no official relations with our Government different from the British
                    commercial agents now there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
